---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Hector, Alicia, and the work" description="About Hector Ouilhet Olmos, Alicia, and the maker-led human-scale AI project.">
  <main class="page-shell about-page">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Hector & Alicia</p>
      <h1>A maker writing from inside the system he built.</h1>
      <p>
        Hector Ouilhet Olmos is building Alicia, a personal AI system, and using
        the trace to write about what AI does to human life at close range.
        Alicia is an interlocutor, mirror, system, archive, and weather-reader.
        Authorship stays with Hector.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">The maker</p>
        <h2>The authority comes from the practice.</h2>
        <p>
          The project starts with the thing itself: the system, its memory, its
          failures, the moments where it helped, and the moments where it
          distorted the view. The essays come from that trace.
        </p>
      </div>
      <figure>
        <img src="/essays/the-weather-between-us/feet-on-raw-stone.jpg" alt="Feet on raw stone inside Luis Barragan's house." />
        <figcaption>Photograph from Luis Barragan's house in Mexico City.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section class="about-grid reverse">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">The system</p>
        <h2>Alicia has been running since January 2026.</h2>
        <p>
          Alicia is open source under MIT. It's built around externalized
          memory, continuity, self-reflection, partnership-level representation,
          and guarded exits. The aim is simple: keep the human legible to
          himself and to the people around him.
        </p>
        <a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/mrdaemoni/myalicia">Open the Alicia repository</a>
      </div>
      <div class="artifact-panel">
        <p class="kicker">Authorship</p>
        <p>The partnership can surface, reflect, and trouble the work. Authorship stays human. The hand stays on the pen.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
